Diabetic Patients: Readmission & Medication Recommendation Analysis

Summary

Innovation: Our project combines collaborative filtering, matrix factorization, and multi-task learning to tackle hospital readmission for diabetic patients.

Background: In the USA, hospital readmissions for diabetic patients cost approximately $30 billion annually (American Diabetes Association). Diabetes is one of the top 3 conditions associated with preventable readmissions. Preventing readmission where unneccessary and controllable can not only benefit hospitals, but also improve patient welfare and healthcare services for all.

Our Multi-Task Framework implements THREE interconnected prediction tasks:

Task Type Target Metrics Concept
Task 1 Classification readmitted_30days ROC-AUC, PR-AUC Binary classification
Task 2 Recommendation Medication effectiveness Precision@K, MAP Collaborative filtering
Task 3 Regression time_in_hospital RMSE, MAE Regularized regression

Key: Joint optimization using multi-task loss: Ltotal=1Lreadmission+2Lmedication+3LLOSLtotal=1Lreadmission+2Lmedication+3LLOS

Section A: Predictive Tasks Definition

Multi-Task Framework

We aim to optimize three interconnected prediction tasks:

  1. Task 1 (Classification): Predict readmitted_30days (binary)

    • Metrics: ROC-AUC, PR-AUC, F1-Score
    • Binary classification with regularization (Chapter 3)

  2. Task 2 (Recommendation): Recommend effective medication changes

    • Metrics: Precision@K, Recall@K, MAP, NDCG
    • Collaborative filtering & ranking (Chapters 8-9)

  3. Task 3 (Regression): Predict optimal time_in_hospital

    • Metrics: RMSE, MAE, R
    • Ridge/Lasso regression (Chapter 3)

Evaluation Strategy

Baselines:

  • Random predictor (lower bound)
  • Majority class predictor
  • Single-task models (Logistic Regression, Random Forest)
  • Prior work benchmark: Strack et al. (~60% accuracy)

Section C: Data Preprocessing & Feature Engineering

Core concepts/implementations:

  1. Bag-of-words style encoding for diagnoses (like text classification)
  2. TF-IDF weighting for medication importance
  3. Sequence features for patient history (e.g. n-grams)
  4. Patient embeddings using Word2Vec (e.g. item2vec)

C.1: Data Cleaning Pipeline (fixed data leakage)

In [49]:
def preprocess_discharge_model(df):
    df = df.copy()
    df = df.replace('?', np.nan)

    # 1) Remove death / hospice
    df = df[~df['discharge_disposition_id'].isin([11, 13, 14, 19, 20, 21])]

    # 2) Keeping first encounter per patient
    df = df.sort_values('encounter_id')
    df = df.drop_duplicates(subset=['patient_nbr'], keep='first').reset_index(drop=True)

    # 3) Target
    df['target'] = (df['readmitted'] == '<30').astype(int)

    # 4) Age
    age_map = {
        '[0-10)': 5, '[10-20)': 15, '[20-30)': 25, '[30-40)': 35, '[40-50)': 45,
        '[50-60)': 55, '[60-70)': 65, '[70-80)': 75, '[80-90)': 85, '[90-100)': 95
    }
    df['age_numeric'] = df['age'].map(age_map)

    # 5) ICD grouping
    def icd_group(code):
        if pd.isna(code) or code == '':
            return 'Other'
        if isinstance(code, str):
            if code.startswith(('V', 'E')):
                return 'Other'
            try:
                n = float(code)
            except:
                return 'Other'
        else:
            n = float(code)

        if 390 <= n <= 459 or n == 785: return 'Circulatory'
        if 460 <= n <= 519 or n == 786: return 'Respiratory'
        if 520 <= n <= 579 or n == 787: return 'Digestive'
        if 250 <= n < 251:            return 'Diabetes'
        if 800 <= n <= 999:           return 'Injury'
        if 710 <= n <= 739:           return 'Musculoskeletal'
        if 580 <= n <= 629 or n == 788: return 'Genitourinary'
        if 140 <= n <= 239:           return 'Neoplasms'
        return 'Other'

    for col in ['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']:
        df[f'{col}_group'] = df[col].apply(icd_group)

    # 6) Medical specialty simplification
    df['medical_specialty'] = df['medical_specialty'].fillna('Missing')
    df['medical_specialty'] = df['medical_specialty'].replace('Missing', 'Unknown')
    top10 = df['medical_specialty'].value_counts().nlargest(10).index
    df['medical_specialty'] = df['medical_specialty'].apply(
        lambda x: x if x in top10 else 'Other'
    )

    # 7) Historical utilization
    df['total_visits_history'] = (
        df['number_outpatient'] +
        df['number_emergency'] +
        df['number_inpatient']
    )
    df['prior_utilization'] = (
        df['number_outpatient'] +
        2 * df['number_emergency'] +
        3 * df['number_inpatient']
    )

    # 8) Discharge-time clinical signals
    df['los'] = df['time_in_hospital']
    df['med_count'] = df['num_medications']
    df['lab_count'] = df['num_lab_procedures']
    df['procedure_count'] = df['num_procedures']
    df['complexity_score'] = df['med_count'] + df['lab_count'] + df['procedure_count']

    # 9) HbA1c / glu control
    df['hba1c_tested'] = (df['A1Cresult'] != 'None').astype(int)
    df['hba1c_abnormal'] = df['A1Cresult'].isin(['>7', '>8']).astype(int)
    df['poor_glucose_control'] = df['max_glu_serum'].isin(['>200', '>300']).astype(int)

    # 10) Diagnosis flags (for diag_1)
    df['has_circulatory'] = (df['diag_1_group'] == 'Circulatory').astype(int)
    df['has_respiratory'] = (df['diag_1_group'] == 'Respiratory').astype(int)
    df['has_diabetes'] = (df['diag_1_group'] == 'Diabetes').astype(int)

    # 11) Medication change numeric features
    change_map = {'Up': 1, 'Down': -1, 'Steady': 0, 'No': 0}
    med_cols = [
        'metformin', 'repaglinide', 'nateglinide', 'chlorpropamide', 'glimepiride',
        'acetohexamide', 'glipizide', 'glyburide', 'tolbutamide', 'pioglitazone',
        'rosiglitazone', 'acarbose', 'miglitol', 'troglitazone', 'tolazamide',
        'examide', 'citoglipton', 'insulin',
        'glyburide-metformin', 'glipizide-metformin',
        'glimepiride-pioglitazone', 'metformin-rosiglitazone',
        'metformin-pioglitazone'
    ]
    for med in med_cols:
        if med in df.columns:
            df[f'{med}_change_num'] = df[med].map(change_map).fillna(0)

    if 'change' in df.columns:
        df['global_med_change'] = df['change'].map(change_map).fillna(0)

    # 12) Drop unused raw columns
    drop_cols = [
        'encounter_id', 'patient_nbr', 'readmitted',
        'diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3',
        'payer_code', 'weight'
    ]
    df = df.drop(columns=drop_cols, errors='ignore')

    print("Final discharge-time dataset:", df.shape)
    print("Target positive rate: {:.2f}%".format(df['target'].mean() * 100))
    return df

df_processed = preprocess_discharge_model(df_raw)

# Patient Embeddings

def create_patient_sequences(df):
    """
    Create 'sentences' of medical events for each patient
    (Similar to item sequences for collaborative filtering)

    Implementation: Word2Vec / item2vec (Chapter 11)
    """
    med_cols = ['metformin', 'repaglinide', 'nateglinide', 'chlorpropamide', 'glimepiride',
                'glipizide', 'glyburide', 'pioglitazone', 'rosiglitazone', 'acarbose',
                'miglitol', 'insulin', 'glyburide-metformin', 'glipizide-metformin']
    available_meds = [c for c in med_cols if c in df.columns]

    sequences = []
    for _, row in df.iterrows():
        seq = []

        # Add diagnosis categories (correcting column names from _cat to _group)
        for diag_col in ['diag_1_group', 'diag_2_group', 'diag_3_group']:
            if diag_col in row.index and pd.notna(row[diag_col]):
                seq.append(f"DIAG_{row[diag_col]}")

        # Add medications with status
        for med in available_meds:
            if med in row.index and row[med] != 'No':
                seq.append(f"{med}_{row[med]}")

        # Add A1C result
        if 'A1Cresult' in row.index:
            a1c = row['A1Cresult']
            if pd.notna(a1c) and a1c != 'None':
                seq.append(f"A1C_{a1c}")
            else:
                seq.append("A1C_None")

        # Add age group
        if 'age_numeric' in row.index and pd.notna(row['age_numeric']):
            age_val = row['age_numeric']
            if age_val < 20: age_grp = 'youth'
            elif age_val < 40: age_grp = 'adult'
            elif age_val < 65: age_grp = 'middle'
            else: age_grp = 'elderly'
            seq.append(f"AGE_{age_grp}")

        # Add gender, race, medical_specialty
        if 'gender' in row.index: seq.append(f"GENDER_{row['gender']}")
        if 'race' in row.index: seq.append(f"RACE_{row['race']}")
        if 'medical_specialty' in row.index: seq.append(f"SPEC_{row['medical_specialty']}")

        # Add admission/discharge related information
        if 'admission_type_id' in row.index: seq.append(f"ADM_TYPE_{row['admission_type_id']}")
        if 'discharge_disposition_id' in row.index: seq.append(f"DIS_DISP_{row['discharge_disposition_id']}")
        if 'admission_source_id' in row.index: seq.append(f"ADM_SRC_{row['admission_source_id']}")

        # Add binned numerical clinical features to enrich sequences
        if 'time_in_hospital' in row.index and pd.notna(row['time_in_hospital']):
            los = row['time_in_hospital']
            if los <= 3: los_grp = 'LOS_short'
            elif los <= 7: los_grp = 'LOS_medium'
            else: los_grp = 'LOS_long'
            seq.append(los_grp)

        if 'num_lab_procedures' in row.index and pd.notna(row['num_lab_procedures']):
            n_lab = row['num_lab_procedures']
            if n_lab <= 30: n_lab_grp = 'LAB_low'
            elif n_lab <= 60: n_lab_grp = 'LAB_medium'
            else: n_lab_grp = 'LAB_high'
            seq.append(n_lab_grp)

        if 'num_procedures' in row.index and pd.notna(row['num_procedures']):
            n_proc = row['num_procedures']
            if n_proc == 0: n_proc_grp = 'PROC_none'
            elif n_proc <= 2: n_proc_grp = 'PROC_few'
            else: n_proc_grp = 'PROC_many'
            seq.append(n_proc_grp)

        if 'number_diagnoses' in row.index and pd.notna(row['number_diagnoses']):
            n_diag = row['number_diagnoses']
            if n_diag <= 5: n_diag_grp = 'DIAG_few'
            elif n_diag <= 8: n_diag_grp = 'DIAG_medium'
            else: n_diag_grp = 'DIAG_many'
            seq.append(n_diag_grp)

        sequences.append(seq)

    return sequences

# Matrix Factorization (Latent Factor Models)

med_cols = ['metformin', 'repaglinide', 'nateglinide', 'chlorpropamide', 'glimepiride',
            'glipizide', 'glyburide', 'pioglitazone', 'rosiglitazone', 'acarbose',
            'miglitol', 'insulin', 'glyburide-metformin', 'glipizide-metformin']
available_meds = [c for c in med_cols if c in df_processed.columns]

# patient  medication matrix w/ effectiveness scores
n_patients = len(df_processed)
n_meds = len(available_meds)
patient_med_matrix = np.zeros((n_patients, n_meds))

for i, (_, row) in enumerate(df_processed.iterrows()):
    for j, med in enumerate(available_meds):
        if row[med] != 'No':
            # Base score for using medication
            score = 1.0
            # Adjusting by dose change only (no outcome leakage)
            if row[med] == 'Up':
                score *= 1.2
            elif row[med] == 'Down':
                score *= 0.9
            patient_med_matrix[i, j] = score

print(f"Matrix shape: {patient_med_matrix.shape}")
print(f"Sparsity: {(patient_med_matrix == 0).sum() / patient_med_matrix.size * 100:.1f}%")

# Application of NMF (Non-negative Matrix Factorization)
n_components = min(10, n_meds - 1)  # Valid num components ensured
nmf = NMF(n_components=n_components, init='nndsvda', random_state=42, max_iter=500)
patient_factors = nmf.fit_transform(patient_med_matrix)  # P: patients  k
medication_factors = nmf.components_                     # Q^T: k  medications

print(f"Patient factors: {patient_factors.shape}")
print(f"Medication factors: {medication_factors.shape}")
print(f"Reconstruction error: {nmf.reconstruction_err_:.4f}")

def prepare_features(df, patient_embeddings=None, patient_factors=None):
    """
    Final feature matrix for discharge-time readmission model.
    """
    feature_list = []
    feature_names = []

    # 1) Numeric features
    numeric_cols = [
        'age_numeric',
        'total_visits_history',
        'prior_utilization',
        'hba1c_tested', 'hba1c_abnormal', 'poor_glucose_control',
        'med_count', 'lab_count', 'procedure_count', 'complexity_score',
        'has_circulatory', 'has_respiratory', 'has_diabetes'
    ]

    for col in numeric_cols:
        if col in df.columns:
            feature_list.append(df[col].fillna(0).values.reshape(-1, 1))
            feature_names.append(col)

    # 2) Medication change numeric features
    med_change_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c.endswith('_change_num')]
    if 'global_med_change' in df.columns:
        med_change_cols.append('global_med_change')

    for col in med_change_cols:
        feature_list.append(df[col].fillna(0).values.reshape(-1, 1))
        feature_names.append(col)

    # 3) Categorical one-hot
    categorical_cols = [
        'race', 'gender', 'medical_specialty',
        'diag_1_group', 'diag_2_group', 'diag_3_group',
        'admission_type_id', 'discharge_disposition_id', 'admission_source_id'
    ]

    for col in categorical_cols:
        if col in df.columns:
            dummies = pd.get_dummies(df[col], prefix=col, drop_first=True)
            feature_list.append(dummies.values)
            feature_names.extend(dummies.columns.tolist())

    # 4) (Optional) embeddings / factors
    if patient_embeddings is not None:
        feature_list.append(patient_embeddings)
        feature_names.extend([f'embed_{i}' for i in range(patient_embeddings.shape[1])])

    if patient_factors is not None:
        feature_list.append(patient_factors)
        feature_names.extend([f'latent_{i}' for i in range(patient_factors.shape[1])])

    # 5) Stack
    X = np.hstack(feature_list)
    X = np.nan_to_num(X, nan=0.0)

    print(f"Final discharge-time feature matrix: {X.shape}")
    print(f"Total features: {len(feature_names)}")
    return X, feature_names

# Use:

# Multi-Task Learning Model

class MultiTaskPredictor:
    """
    Multi-task model for simultaneous prediction of:
    1. Readmission (classification)
    2. Length of stay (regression)
    
    CSE 158 Connection: Shared representations, multi-output learning (Ch. 3)
    """
    
    def __init__(self, lambda_class=1.0, lambda_reg=0.5, C=1.0, alpha=1.0):
        self.lambda_class = lambda_class
        self.lambda_reg = lambda_reg
        self.classifier = LogisticRegression(C=C, max_iter=1000, random_state=42,
                                             class_weight='balanced')
        self.regressor = Ridge(alpha=alpha)
        self.scaler = StandardScaler()
    
    def fit(self, X, y_class, y_reg):
        X_scaled = self.scaler.fit_transform(X)
        
        # Train classifier
        self.classifier.fit(X_scaled, y_class)
        
        # Use classifier predictions as feature for regressor (multi-task coupling)
        class_proba = self.classifier.predict_proba(X_scaled)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
        X_reg = np.hstack([X_scaled, class_proba])
        
        # Train regressor
        self.regressor.fit(X_reg, y_reg)
        return self
    
    def predict_readmission(self, X):
        X_scaled = self.scaler.transform(X)
        return self.classifier.predict_proba(X_scaled)[:, 1]
    
    def predict_los(self, X):
        X_scaled = self.scaler.transform(X)
        class_proba = self.classifier.predict_proba(X_scaled)[:, 1].reshape(-1, 1)
        X_reg = np.hstack([X_scaled, class_proba])
        return self.regressor.predict(X_reg)
    
    def predict(self, X):
        return {
            'readmission_prob': self.predict_readmission(X),
            'los_pred': self.predict_los(X)
        }

# Train multi-task model
mt_model = MultiTaskPredictor(lambda_class=1.0, lambda_reg=0.3, C=best_C, alpha=1)
mt_model.fit(X_train, y_train_readmit, y_train_los)

# Collaborative Filtering Recommender

class CollaborativeFilteringRecommender:
    """
    User-User Collaborative Filtering for Medication Recommendations.
    Patients = Users, Medications = Items
    
    CSE 158 Connection: Chapter 9 - Collaborative Filtering
    """
    
    def __init__(self, k_neighbors=20):
        self.k_neighbors = k_neighbors
        self.embeddings = None
        self.medications = None
        self.med_names = None
        self.outcomes = None
        self.similarity = None
    
    def fit(self, embeddings, medications, med_names, outcomes=None):
        self.embeddings = embeddings
        self.medications = medications
        self.med_names = med_names
        self.outcomes = outcomes
        self.similarity = cosine_similarity(embeddings)
        np.fill_diagonal(self.similarity, 0)
        return self
    
    def recommend(self, patient_idx, top_n=5, filter_used=True):
        similarities = self.similarity[patient_idx]
        top_k_idx = np.argsort(similarities)[::-1][:self.k_neighbors]
        top_k_sim = similarities[top_k_idx]
        
        med_scores = np.zeros(len(self.med_names))
        
        for neighbor_idx, sim in zip(top_k_idx, top_k_sim):
            if sim <= 0:
                continue
            weight = sim
            # Prefer medications from non-readmitted patients
            if self.outcomes is not None and self.outcomes[neighbor_idx] == 0:
                weight *= 1.5
            med_scores += weight * self.medications[neighbor_idx]
        
        if filter_used:
            current = self.medications[patient_idx]
            med_scores[current > 0] = -np.inf
        
        top_n_idx = np.argsort(med_scores)[::-1][:top_n]
        return [(self.med_names[i], med_scores[i]) for i in top_n_idx if med_scores[i] > 0]

# Prepare medication matrix
med_matrix_binary = (patient_med_matrix > 0).astype(float)

# Train recommender
cf_recommender = CollaborativeFilteringRecommender(k_neighbors=30)
cf_recommender.fit(
    embeddings=patient_embeddings,
    medications=med_matrix_binary,
    med_names=available_meds,
    outcomes=y_readmission
)

print(" Collaborative Filtering Recommender trained")

# Example recommendation
example_idx = np.random.choice(len(patient_embeddings))
print(f"\nExample: Recommendations for Patient {example_idx}")
current_meds = [available_meds[i] for i in range(len(available_meds)) if med_matrix_binary[example_idx, i] > 0]
print(f"Current medications: {current_meds}")

E.1: Recommendation Metrics (Precision@K, MAP, NDCG)

In [64]:
# Recommendation Metrics

def precision_at_k(recommended, ground_truth, k):
    """Precision@K: Of top K recommended, how many are relevant?"""
    if len(recommended) == 0:
        return 0.0
    rec_k = set(recommended[:k])
    relevant = set(ground_truth)
    return len(rec_k & relevant) / len(rec_k) if rec_k else 0.0

def recall_at_k(recommended, ground_truth, k):
    """Recall@K: Of all relevant, how many are in top K?"""
    if len(ground_truth) == 0:
        return 0.0
    rec_k = set(recommended[:k])
    relevant = set(ground_truth)
    return len(rec_k & relevant) / len(relevant)

def average_precision(recommended, ground_truth):
    """Average Precision for a single query"""
    if len(ground_truth) == 0:
        return 0.0
    relevant = set(ground_truth)
    score = 0.0
    hits = 0
    for i, item in enumerate(recommended):
        if item in relevant:
            hits += 1
            score += hits / (i + 1)
    return score / len(relevant)

def ndcg_at_k(recommended, ground_truth, k):
    """Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain @ K"""
    relevant = set(ground_truth)
    dcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 2) for i, item in enumerate(recommended[:k]) if item in relevant)
    idcg = sum(1.0 / np.log2(i + 2) for i in range(min(len(relevant), k)))
    return dcg / idcg if idcg > 0 else 0.0

def mean_average_precision(recommendations_list, ground_truth_list):
    """MAP across all queries"""
    return np.mean([average_precision(r, g) for r, g in zip(recommendations_list, ground_truth_list)])

def classification_report_full(y_true, y_prob, threshold=0.5):
    y_pred = (y_prob >= threshold).astype(int)

    acc = accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred)
    prec = precision_score(y_true, y_pred, zero_division=0)
    rec = recall_score(y_true, y_pred)
    f1 = f1_score(y_true, y_pred)

    tn, fp, fn, tp = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred).ravel()
    specificity = tn / (tn + fp)

    return {
        'accuracy': acc,
        'precision': prec,
        'recall': rec,
        'specificity': specificity,
        'f1': f1,
        'tp': tp,
        'fp': fp,
        'fn': fn,
        'tn': tn
    }

def count_positive_predictions(y_prob, threshold=0.5):
    y_pred = (y_prob >= threshold).astype(int)
    count_pos = y_pred.sum()
    count_neg = len(y_pred) - count_pos
    return count_pos, count_neg

def best_threshold(y_true, y_prob):
    precision, recall, thresholds = precision_recall_curve(y_true, y_prob)
    f1 = 2 * (precision * recall) / (precision + recall + 1e-9)
    idx = np.argmax(f1)
    return thresholds[idx], precision[idx], recall[idx], f1[idx]

# Medication Recommender Eval

def evaluate_recommender(recommender, med_matrix, med_names, n_eval=1000, k=5, seed=42):
    """
    Evaluate recommender using leave-one-out methodology.
    For each patient with 2+ medications:
      1. Hide one medication
      2. Generate recommendations
      3. Check if hidden medication appears in top-K
    """
    np.random.seed(seed)
    
    # Find patients with at least 2 medications
    patient_med_counts = med_matrix.sum(axis=1)
    eligible_patients = np.where(patient_med_counts >= 2)[0]
    
    # Sample for efficiency
    eval_patients = np.random.choice(eligible_patients, 
                                     min(n_eval, len(eligible_patients)), 
                                     replace=False)
    
    hits_at_k = 0
    reciprocal_ranks = []
    precisions = []
    
    for patient_idx in eval_patients:
        # Get patient's actual medications
        actual_meds = np.where(med_matrix[patient_idx] > 0)[0]
        if len(actual_meds) < 2:
            continue
            
        # Hide one medication (the "ground truth")
        hidden_med_idx = np.random.choice(actual_meds)
        hidden_med = med_names[hidden_med_idx]
        
        # Temporarily remove the hidden medication
        original_value = recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx]
        recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx] = 0
        
        # Get recommendations
        recs = recommender.recommend(patient_idx, top_n=k, filter_used=True)
        rec_names = [r[0] for r in recs]
        
        # Restore the hidden medication
        recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx] = original_value
        
        # Evaluate
        if hidden_med in rec_names:
            hits_at_k += 1
            rank = rec_names.index(hidden_med) + 1
            reciprocal_ranks.append(1.0 / rank)
            precisions.append(1.0 / k)
        else:
            reciprocal_ranks.append(0.0)
            precisions.append(0.0)
    
    # Calculate metrics
    hit_rate = hits_at_k / len(eval_patients)
    mrr = np.mean(reciprocal_ranks)
    precision_at_k = np.mean(precisions)
    
    return {
        'Hit Rate@K': hit_rate,
        'MRR': mrr,
        'Precision@K': precision_at_k,
        'Evaluated Patients': len(eval_patients)
    }

# Run evaluation

# Deeper Recommender Evaluation

def detailed_recommender_evaluation(recommender, med_matrix, med_names, n_eval=2000, seed=42):
    """More rigorous evaluation with multiple checks."""
    np.random.seed(seed)
    
    patient_med_counts = med_matrix.sum(axis=1)
    eligible_patients = np.where(patient_med_counts >= 2)[0]
    eval_patients = np.random.choice(eligible_patients, 
                                     min(n_eval, len(eligible_patients)), 
                                     replace=False)
    
    results_by_med = {med: {'hidden': 0, 'recovered': 0} for med in med_names}
    results_by_k = {k: 0 for k in [1, 3, 5, 10]}
    
    for patient_idx in eval_patients:
        actual_meds = np.where(med_matrix[patient_idx] > 0)[0]
        if len(actual_meds) < 2:
            continue
            
        hidden_med_idx = np.random.choice(actual_meds)
        hidden_med = med_names[hidden_med_idx]
        
        original_value = recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx]
        recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx] = 0
        
        recs = recommender.recommend(patient_idx, top_n=10, filter_used=True)
        rec_names = [r[0] for r in recs]
        
        recommender.medications[patient_idx, hidden_med_idx] = original_value
        
        # Track by medication
        results_by_med[hidden_med]['hidden'] += 1
        if hidden_med in rec_names[:5]:
            results_by_med[hidden_med]['recovered'] += 1
        
        # Track by K
        for k in results_by_k.keys():
            if hidden_med in rec_names[:k]:
                results_by_k[k] += 1
    
    return results_by_med, results_by_k, len(eval_patients)

# Case Study: Patient Predications

def show_patient_prediction(patient_idx, df, mt_model, cf_recommender, X_test, available_meds, test_index_lookup):
    """
    Show detailed prediction for one patient with interpretability.
    """
    print("=" * 60)
    print(f"CASE STUDY: Patient {patient_idx}")
    print("=" * 60)
    
    # Get patient data
    patient = df.iloc[patient_idx]
    
    print("\nPatient Profile:")
    print(f"   Age: {patient.get('age_numeric', 'N/A')} years")
    print(f"   Gender: {patient.get('gender', 'N/A')}")
    print(f"   Primary Diagnosis: {patient.get('diag_1_cat', 'N/A')}")
    print(f"   Number of Medications: {patient.get('num_medications', 'N/A')}")
    print(f"   Prior Inpatient Visits: {patient.get('number_inpatient', 'N/A')}")
    print(f"   HbA1c Result: {patient.get('A1Cresult', 'N/A')}")
    
    # Actual outcome
    actual_readmit = patient.get('readmitted_30days', 'N/A')
    actual_los = patient.get('time_in_hospital', 'N/A')
    
    print(f"\nActual Outcomes:")
    print(f"   Readmitted <30 days: {'Yes' if actual_readmit == 1 else 'No'}")
    print(f"   Length of Stay: {actual_los} days")
    
    # Model predictions
    test_pos = test_index_lookup.get(patient_idx)
    if test_pos is not None:
        preds = mt_model.predict(X_test[test_pos:test_pos+1])
        pred_prob = preds['readmission_prob'][0]
        pred_los = preds['los_pred'][0]
        
        print(f"\nModel Predictions:")
        print(f"   Readmission Probability: {pred_prob*100:.1f}%")
        risk_level = "HIGH" if pred_prob > 0.3 else "MEDIUM" if pred_prob > 0.15 else "LOW"
        print(f"   Risk Level: {risk_level}")
        print(f"   Predicted LOS: {pred_los:.1f} days")
    else:
        print(f"\nModel Predictions:")
        print("   Patient not in held-out test set; prediction unavailable in this view")
    
    # Medication recommendations
    print(f"\nMedication Recommendations:")
    try:
        recs = cf_recommender.recommend(patient_idx, top_n=3)
        if recs:
            for i, (med, score) in enumerate(recs, 1):
                print(f"   {i}. {med} (confidence: {score:.2f})")
        else:
            print("   No new medications recommended")
    except Exception as exc:
        print(f"   Unable to generate recommendations ({exc})")
    
    print("\n" + "=" * 60)

# Show case studies for different risk levels
print("\n" + "#" * 70)
